name: facts-protocol-wiki
settings: The objective of the facts protocol is to disintermediate (remove gatekeepers from) the truth. The facts protocol is a decentralized, open source, community driven, and censorship resistant protocol for determining the truth. It consists of a set of rules and incentives that govern the creation, distribution, and consumption of facts. As a framework, the facts protocol aims to facilitate a transparent and reliable system for sharing and evaluating information. This wiki adheres to open source governance and community driven development, encouraging collaboration and contribution from users to ensure its continuous improvement and relevance.
